```json
{
"application": "SLURM",
"other_software": [
"Python/3.5.2-intel-2017.u2-GCC-5.4.0-CUDA9",
"nvidia-smi",
"coconut_train.py"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"nodes": 1,
"partition": "gpgpu",
"gres": "gpu:p100:4",
"ntasks": 1,
"cpus-per-task": 12,
"mem": "32G",
"time": "48:00:00"
}
}
```

This script is designed to run on the SLURM job scheduler. It requests a single node from the "gpgpu" partition with four P100 GPUs, uses 12 CPU cores per task with 32GB of memory per process, and runs for a maximum of 48 hours. 

The script loads the Python/3.5.2-intel-2017.u2-GCC-5.4.0-CUDA9 module, uses the nvidia-smi command to check GPU information, and runs the "coconut_train.py" script with specific parameters related to training a model on a dataset called "food179".
